    "summary": "Experienced Board member, Manager and Consultant in the Public Sector for Ministries, Provinces, Universities, Local Municipalities and the culture and leisure sector. The main emphasis lays at business operations and organizational change particularly focused on the support of the top and middle management. Assignments both from national and international organizations.\n\nSince 2018 Jeroen van Spijk works for the Galan Groep in various roles as advisor, interim manager, lobbyist and director. He works for all levels of government, the cultural sector, universities and NGOs with a particular focus on spacial planning.\n\nIn the period 2014-2018 Jeroen van Spijk was Alderman for the city of Haarlem responsible for Spatial Planning (real estate development), Monument, Amsterdam Metropolitan Area, Deregulation, Services, Citizen Participation, Europe, Finance and Business Operations.\n\nIn the period 2010-2014 Alderman for the city of Amsterdam district East responsible for Finance, Cultural affairs, Transport, The catering industry and tourism. One of the achievements was the financial merger of two former city districts plus the development of new financial tools for citizens involvement.\n\nNext to the professional career member of various boards in the City of Amsterdam. This includes chairman of the political party D66 and board member of the Hortus Botanicus Amsterdam.\n\nSpecialisms: Business Operations, Real Estate, Spatial Planning, Finance, Decentralization, Risk Management and Process Optimization of the Administrative Organization",
